reut2-021.sgm, INDIAN RESERVE BANK TIGHTENS CREDIT POLICY, The Reserve Bank of India said it wastightening its credit policy for commercial banks by raisingtheir cash reserve ratio by 0.5 pct to 10 pct, effective fromOctober 24.    The move, announced last weekend, is part of the bank'spolicy for the second half of fiscal 1987/88 ending March andis aimed at curbing excess bank liquidity.    The central bank also put selective controls on bankadvances to the oilseeds, vegetable oils and foodgrains trades.    The policy's main objective is to fully meet the creditrequirements of agriculture

